# ðŸ”’ Privacy Policy - Fortyra Bot

**Last Updated:** 19-05-2025

This Privacy Policy explains how **Fortyra** ("the Bot", "we", "our") collects, uses, and stores data when you interact with it in Discord.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

The Bot may collect the following data:

- **User Identifiers**  
  - Discord User ID  
  - Guild (Server) ID  
  - Channel IDs (for context-specific commands)  
  - Message IDs (for moderation and logging)

- **Command Usage**  
  - Commands executed  
  - Timestamps of usage  
  - Success/failure status

- **Server Configuration Data**  
  - Moderation settings  
  - Logging channel IDs  
  - Feature toggles and preferences

> _We **do not** collect personal messages, passwords, or sensitive personal information._

---

## 2. Why We Collect Data

Data is collected for the following purposes:

- To provide bot functionality (commands, moderation, etc.)
- To save custom server settings
- To monitor performance and detect abuse
- To improve features based on usage statistics

---

## 3. Data Storage

- Data is stored securely using [your storage system, e.g., MongoDB, better-sqlite3].
- Only authorized developers have access to this data.
- We do **not** share or sell any user data to third parties.

---

## 4. Data Retention

- Server and user configuration data are stored until removed by a server administrator or the bot is removed.
- Temporary data (like cooldowns or session tokens) may be stored for a limited time (e.g., minutes or hours).

---

## 5. User Control & Rights

As a Discord user, you may:

- Request deletion of your stored data by contacting the developers
- Reset your server configuration using in-bot commands (if applicable)
- Remove the bot to halt all data collection in your server

---

## 6. Third-Party Services

If the bot integrates with third-party APIs (e.g., YouTube, Reddit, etc.), you are subject to those services' privacy policies. We do not control third-party data policies.

---

## 7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted in the official support server and/or GitHub repository.

---

